[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      164[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Amazon DynamoDB for schedule state.** Nurses check the schedule board constantly. The patient portal refreshes every 30 seconds. Pharmacy needs instant visibility into timing changes. You need single-digit-millisecond reads on a data structure that updates maybe 50 times per day but gets read thousands of times. DynamoDB's read performance and conditional writes (preventing race conditions when multiple adjustments happen simultaneously) fit this access pattern exactly.
